{
  "stem": "21437.1",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And I think they were children, again-- because they were really born in Poland and attended Polish schools, really they were very-- they didn't have that inner security of knowing the language, the Polish language fluently either.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 64,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Very strongly.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 64,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I mean, they were-- they were more than traditional.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 64,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They were religious.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 64,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Not in dress, but otherwise everything was observed.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 64,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And our life was governed by the Jewish laws.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 65,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was, I think, the way the tone of the voice-- of their voices.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 65,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "For instance, like my grandfather who had 18 grandchildren.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 65,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I think 18.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 65,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He was-- he-- we didn't live in the same town.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 65,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He lived about 3/4 of an hour away in Bedzin.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 65,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But he would come at least once a week and sit with me for at least three hours, two or three hours, just with me, and read to me.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 65,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Take the Siddur, interpret from the Siddur.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 65,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I think that as he was interpreting to me, he was sort of weaving his own story into it as well.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 65,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And it was somehow-- the way I perceived it, that it was all about love and peace.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 65,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So really, he-- he instilled in me that feeling and the love for peace, for inner peace, particularly.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 65,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "As he particularly-- as he was a very-- really a very gentle person.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 65,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "He was very intelligent and very perceptive.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 65,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "I realized later on-- because my mother was his daughter-in-law.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 65,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "But somehow he never-- it never ceased to-- cease to amaze me the way he talked about my mother.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 65,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "How important she was to him.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 66,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Icie Mayer.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 67,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Icie.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 67,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I-C-I-E-.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 67,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Mayer.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 67,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The way he spelled it with a-- M-A-Y-E-R. -E-R.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 67,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Siegreich.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 68,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 69,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 69,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Well, the synagogue was quite far from us.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
